@Al  in Pittsburgh

Baseball is virtually unknown here. Last I checked there were 8 full sized baseball fields in Poland, and none in Warsaw (there is a football, as in:soccer, pitch in every town and city, and many villages) . I've never seen baseball on TV here, and it never made it to the sport section of the news when I still watched it a decade or two ago. I'd bet all my money less than 0,01% of Poles can name a single baseball player. Other than Babe Ruth and DiMaggio, who pop up in films and tv often enough, I've heard of no baseball players before I started doing these puzzles.

@Francis

